}} }} 'Historic Jamestowne' is the official name used for promotional purposes
for the original site of the 1607 James Fort and the later 17th century city of
Jamestown. It is located on the James River at Jamestown, Virginia and operated
as a partnership between Preservation Virginia (formerly known as the
Association for the Preservation of Virginia Antiquities) and the U.S. National
Park Service. The mission of Historic Jamestowne is to "preserve, protect and
promote the original site of the first permanent English settlement in North
America and to tell the story of the role of the three cultures, European, North
American and African, that came together to lay the foundation for a uniquely
American form of democratic government, language, free enterprise and
society."
